obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (49774)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 10th January, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 135(E), dated 10th January, 2020, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 2(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49774&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Transgender Persons (Protection of Rights) Act, 2019.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (49775)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49775&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appropriate Government" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to the Central Government or any establishment, wholly or substantially`
  line `financed by that Government, the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to a State Government or any establishment, wholly or substantially financed`
  line `by that Government, or any local authority, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) "establishment" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any body or authority established by or under a Central Act or a State Act or an authority`
  line `or a body owned or controlled or aided by the Government or a local authority, or a Government`
  line `company as defined in section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), and includes a`
  line `Department of the Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any company or body corporate or association or body of individuals, firm, cooperative or`
  line `other society, association, trust, agency, institution;`
  line
  line `(c) "family" means a group of people related by blood or marriage or by adoption made in`
  line `accordance with law;`
  line
  line `(d) "inclusive education" means a system of education wherein transgender students learn`
  line `together with other students without fear of discrimination, neglect, harassment or intimidation and`
  line `the system of teaching and learning is suitably adapted to meet the learning needs of such students;`
  line
  line `(e) "institution" means an institution, whether public or private, for the reception, care, protection,`
  line `education, training or any other service of transgender persons;`
  line
  line `(f) "local authority" means the municipal corporation or Municipality or Panchayat or any other`
  line `local body constituted under any law for the time being in force for providing municipal services or`
  line `basic services, as the case may be, in respect of areas under its jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(g) "National Council" means the National Council for Transgender Persons established under`
  line `section 16;`
  line
  line `(h) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(i) "person with intersex variations" means a person who at birth shows variation in his or her`
  line `primary sexual characteristics, external genitalia, chromosomes or hormones from normative standard`
  line `of male or female body;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the appropriate Government under this Act;`
  line and
  line
  line `(k) "transgender person" means a person whose gender does not match with the gender assigned`
  line `to that person at birth and includes trans-man or trans-woman (whether or not such person has`
  line `undergone Sex Reassignment Surgery or hormone therapy or laser therapy or such other therapy),`
  line `person with intersex variations, genderqueer and person having such socio-cultural identities as`
  line `kinner, hijra, aravani and jogta.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (49776)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition against discrimination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49776&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `No person or establishment shall discriminate against a`
  line `transgender person on any of the following grounds, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the denial, or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment in, educational establishments and`
  line `services thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the unfair treatment in, or in relation to, employment or occupation;`
  line
  line `(c) the denial of, or termination from, employment or occupation;`
  line
  line `(d) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment in, healthcare services;`
  line
  line `(e) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment with regard to, access to, or provision or`
  line `enjoyment or use of any goods, accommodation, service, facility, benefit, privilege or opportunity`
  line `dedicated to the use of the general public or customarily available to the public;`
  line
  line `(f) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment with regard to the right of movement;`
  line
  line `(g) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment with regard to the right to reside,`
  line `purchase, rent, or otherwise occupy any property;`
  line
  line `(h) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment in, the opportunity to stand for or hold`
  line `public or private office; and`
  line
  line `(i) the denial of access to, removal from, or unfair treatment in, Government or private`
  line `establishment in whose care or custody a transgender person may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (49777)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Recognition of identity of transgender person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49777&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) A transgender person shall have a right to`
  line `be recognised as such, in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person recognised as transgender under sub-section (1) shall have a right to self-perceived`
  line `gender identity.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (49778)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Application for certificate of identity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49778&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A transgender person may make an application to the`
  line `District Magistrate for issuing a certificate of identity as a transgender person, in such form and manner,`
  line `and accompanied with such documents, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a minor child, such application shall be made by a parent or guardian of`
  line `such child.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (49779)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Issue of certificate of identity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49779&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The District Magistrate shall issue to the applicant under`
  line `section 5, a certificate of identity as transgender person after following such procedure and in such form`
  line `and manner, within such time, as may be prescribed indicating the gender of such person as transgender.`
  line
  line `(2) The gender of transgender person shall be recorded in all official documents in accordance with`
  line `certificate issued under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) A certificate issued to a person under sub-section (1) shall confer rights and be a proof of`
  line `recognition of his identity as a transgender person.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (49780)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Change in gender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49780&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the issue of a certificate under sub-section (1) of section 6, if a transgender person undergoes surgery to change gender either as a male or female, such person may make an application, along with a certificate issued to that effect by the Medical Superintendent or Chief Medical Officer of the medical institution in which that person has undergone surgery, to the District Magistrate for revised certificate, in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The District Magistrate shall, on receipt of an application along with the certificate issued by the Medical Superintendent or Chief Medical Officer, and on being satisfied with the correctness of such certificate, issue a certificate indicating change in gender in such form and manner and within such time, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The person who has been issued a certificate of identity under section 6 or a revised certificate under sub-section (2) shall be entitled to change the first name in the birth certificate and all other official documents relating to the identity of such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that such change in gender and the issue of revised certificate under sub-section (2) shall not affect the rights and entitlements of such person under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (49781)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Obligation of appropriate Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49781&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government shall take steps to`
  line `secure full and effective participation of transgender persons and their inclusion in society.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall take such welfare measures as may be prescribed to protect the`
  line `rights and interests of transgender persons, and facilitate their access to welfare schemes framed by that`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The appropriate Government shall formulate welfare schemes and programmes which are`
  line `transgender sensitive, non-stigmatising and non-discriminatory.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government shall take steps for the rescue, protection and rehabilitation of`
  line `transgender persons to address the needs of such persons.`
  line
  line `(5) The appropriate Government shall take appropriate measures to promote and protect the right of`
  line `transgender persons to participate in cultural and recreational activities.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (49782)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Non-discrimination in employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49782&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No establishment shall discriminate against any`
  line `transgender person in any matter relating to employment including, but not limited to, recruitment,`
  line `promotion and other related issues.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (49783)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Obligations of establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49783&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every establishment shall ensure compliance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and provide such facilities to transgender persons as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (49784)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Grievance redressal mechanism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49784&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every establishment shall designate a person to be a`
  line `complaint officer to deal with the complaints relating to violation of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (49785)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Right of residence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49785&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) No child shall be separated from parents or immediate family on the`
  line `ground of being a transgender, except on an order of a competent court, in the interest of such child.`
  line
  line `(2) Every transgender person shall have---`
  line
  line `(a) a right to reside in the household where parent or immediate family members reside;`
  line
  line `(b) a right not to be excluded from such household or any part thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) a right to enjoy and use the facilities of such household in a non-discriminatory manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any parent or a member of his immediate family is unable to take care of a transgender, the`
  line `competent court shall by an order direct such person to be placed in rehabilitation centre.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (49786)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Obligation of educational institutions to provide inclusive education to transgender persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49786&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every educational institution funded or recognised by the appropriate Government shall`
  line `provide inclusive education and opportunities for sports, recreation and leisure activities to transgender`
  line `persons without discrimination on an equal basis with others.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (49787)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Vocational training and self-employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49787&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall formulate`
  line `welfare schemes and programmes to facilitate and support livelihood for transgender persons including`
  line `their vocational training and self-employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (49788)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Healthcare facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49788&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government shall take the following measures in relation`
  line `to transgender persons, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to set up separate human immunodeficiency virus Sero-surveillance Centres to conduct serosurveillance for such persons in accordance with the guidelines issued by the National AIDS Control`
  line `Organisation in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide for medical care facility including sex reassignment surgery and hormonal therapy;`
  line
  line `(c) before and after sex reassignment surgery and hormonal therapy counselling;`
  line
  line `(d) bring out a Health Manual related to sex reassignment surgery in accordance with the World`
  line `Profession Association for Transgender Health guidelines;`
  line
  line `(e) review of medical curriculum and research for doctors to address their specific health issues;`
  line
  line `(f) to facilitate access to transgender persons in hospitals and other healthcare institutions and`
  line centres;
  line
  line `(g) provision for coverage of medical expenses by a comprehensive insurance scheme for Sex`
  line `Reassignment Surgery, hormonal therapy, laser therapy or any other health issues of transgender`
  line persons.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (49789)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `National Council for Transgender Persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49789&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall by notification`
  line `constitute a National Council for Transgender Persons to exercise the powers conferred on, and to`
  line `perform the functions assigned to it, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Council shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) the Union Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment,`
  line `Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister of State, in-charge of the Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment in the`
  line `Government, Vice-Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary to the Government of India in-charge of the Ministry of Social Justice and`
  line `Empowerment, Member, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) one representative each from the Ministries of Health and Family Welfare, Home Affairs,`
  line `Housing and Urban Affairs, Minority Affairs, Human Resources Development, Rural Development,`
  line `Labour and Employment and Departments of Legal Affairs, Pensions and Pensioners Welfare and`
  line `National Institute for Transforming India Aayog, not below the rank of Joint Secretaries to the`
  line `Government of India, Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) one representative each from the National Human Rights Commission and National`
  line `Commission for Women, not below the rank of Joint Secretaries to the Government of India,`
  line `Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) representatives of the State Governments and Union territories by rotation, one each from the`
  line `North, South, East, West and North-East regions, to be nominated by the Central Government,`
  line `Members, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) five representatives of transgender community, by rotation, from the State Governments and`
  line `Union territories, one each from the North, South, East, West and North-East regions, to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government, Members;`
  line
  line `(h) five experts, to represent non-governmental organisations or associations, working for the`
  line `welfare of transgender persons, to be nominated by the Central Government, Members; and`
  line
  line `(i) Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Social Justice and Empowerment`
  line `dealing with the welfare of the transgender persons, Member Secretary, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) A Member of National Council, other than ex officio member, shall hold office for a term of three`
  line `years from the date of his nomination.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (49790)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Functions of Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49790&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The National Council shall perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) to advise the Central Government on the formulation of policies, programmes, legislation and`
  line `projects with respect to transgender persons;`
  line
  line `(b) to monitor and evaluate the impact of policies and programmes designed for achieving`
  line `equality and full participation of transgender persons;`
  line
  line `(c) to review and coordinate the activities of all the departments of Government and other`
  line `Governmental and non-Governmental Organisations which are dealing with matters relating to`
  line `transgender persons;`
  line
  line `(d) to redress the grievances of transgender persons; and`
  line
  line `(e) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (49791)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49791&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line Whoever,—
  line
  line `(a) compels or entices a transgender person to indulge in the act of forced or bonded labour other`
  line `than any compulsory service for public purposes imposed by Government;`
  line
  line `(b) denies a transgender person the right of passage to a public place or obstructs such person`
  line `from using or having access to a public place to which other members have access to or a right to use;`
  line
  line `(c) forces or causes a transgender person to leave household, village or other place of residence;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) harms or injures or endangers the life, safety, health or well-being, whether mental or`
  line `physical, of a transgender person or tends to do acts including causing physical abuse, sexual abuse,`
  line `verbal and emotional abuse and economic abuse, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to two years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (49792)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49792&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, from time to time, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, credit such sums to the National Council as may`
  line `be necessary for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (49793)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Act not in derogation of any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49793&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (49794)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49794&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the appropriate Government or any local authority or any officer of the Government in respect`
  line `of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of the provisions of this Act`
  line `and any rules made there under.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (49795)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49795&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may,`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which an application shall be made under section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure, form and manner and the period within which a certificate of identity is issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which an application shall be made under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the form, period and manner for issuing revised certificate under sub-section (2) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(e) welfare measures to be provided under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(f) facilities to be provided under section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) other functions of the National Council under clause (e) of section 17; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under sub-section (1), shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the State Government under sub-section (1), shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (49796)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013&sectionId=49796&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00007_201940_1579157374013
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of the period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
